docker build -t <docekrimage name> .  ----build image
docker ps --- show ruuning image container
docker run -dp 127.0.0.1:3000:3000 getting-started ---- for run the image and -d flag 
is used for detech and -p is flag
used for mapping port of local and container ports.

docker stop <container ID> its the container(running image ) then we can remove the image
docker rm <container ID>
docker rm -f <container ID>
docker rmi <Image>-----To remove image 
docker rm -f $(docker ps -aq) -----------this command remove all container (images)

=== if you are using diffrent platform then you can use this command.

docker build --platform linux/amd64 -t YOUR-USER-NAME/getting-started.

